<br>
In time they'll put newer ones that are better, upgrade the ones existing, and figure out that they're all no drop even though the bazaar has a Charm slot listed to trade (yeah I know its for the RP server but still). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13427<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/03 10:09 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charming</span><hr size=1> The Shimmering Emerald Charm is actually pretty nice. I had a momentary pang when switching it out for the PoP charm (for which I got 5 AA, so it's not the beginner model). Spell Haste II is nice, and I love me some MR.<br>
<br>
And the trick to finding the captain is to kill JUST his PH, then go into town and do other things, like kill other stuff in Dulak for a charm. You can get the Purple Tipped Orchid and Charm of the Brotherhood insanely easy in Dulak, as well as the Carved Fox's Ear. Four charms, one zone. I have two of them, myself, and wasn't even trying for the Charm of Brotherhood.<br>
<br>
And now that the Charm of Brotherhood works off your same race as well as class, you can actually see the stats go up -- mage in my guild got it to the fourth level in a Valor group last night without trying. (He only has one PoP flag, and isn't enamored of that charm.) <p><a href="http://www.EQPixelArmy.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-animation.gif" height="120" width="80" alt="EQPA" border=0></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41790" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-text.gif" height=120 width=272 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Warriors ph34r me!<BR>Gnomercy for Gno-one!</span><br>  Posts: 2223<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/03 10:31 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: easy to get wizard charms? </span><hr size=1> If you don't have any flags yet, then there is a really nice charm you can get that increases in power depending on how much plat you have in the bank.<br>
